---
import Base from '@/layouts/Base.astro';
import PageHeader from '@/components/PageHeader.astro';
import EmailSignup from '@/components/EmailSignup.tsx';
import { site } from '@/lib/site';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy notice"
  description="How Fair Food Pricing handles your data. No cookies on first visit. No third-party trackers. Letters generated client-side."
>
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="Plain English"
    title="Privacy notice"
    intro="What we collect, what we do with it, and how to complain if you think we’ve got it wrong."
  />

  <article class="container-prose prose prose-neutral [&_a]:text-primary max-w-none py-10">
    <p>Last updated: <time datetime="2026-05-17">17 May 2026</time>.</p>

    <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
    <p>
      This website is published by <strong>{site.publisher.name}</strong>, acting as the data
      controller. Contact: <a href={`mailto:${site.publisher.email}`}>{site.publisher.email}</a>.
      {site.publisher.affiliation}
    </p>

    <h2>2. What we collect — and what we don’t</h2>
    <p>This site is deliberately minimal. The full data inventory:</p>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full border-collapse text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-rule border-b text-left">
            <th class="py-2 pr-3 font-semibold">Data</th>
            <th class="py-2 pr-3 font-semibold">Where it goes</th>
            <th class="py-2 pr-3 font-semibold">How long</th>
            <th class="py-2 font-semibold">Lawful basis</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="align-top">
          <tr class="border-rule border-b">
            <td class="py-3 pr-3">Postcode (MP finder)</td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-3"
              >Sent to <a href="https://postcodes.io" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"
                >api.postcodes.io</a
              > for constituency lookup. Not stored on our side.</td
            >
            <td class="py-3 pr-3">Not retained</td>
            <td class="py-3">Legitimate interests — transparent constituency lookup</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-rule border-b">
            <td class="py-3 pr-3">Constituency name</td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-3">Sent to the official UK Parliament Members API.</td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-3">Not retained</td>
            <td class="py-3">Legitimate interests — public-record API call</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-rule border-b">
            <td class="py-3 pr-3">Letter contents</td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-3">Generated entirely in your browser. Never sent to our server.</td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-3">Not retained</td>
            <td class="py-3">N/A — no transfer to us</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-rule border-b">
            <td class="py-3 pr-3">IP address</td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-3">Cloudflare CDN edge logs (abuse prevention only).</td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-3">7 days</td>
            <td class="py-3">Legitimate interests — security</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="py-3 pr-3">Email address (if you opt in)</td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-3">
              Email-list signup is in development. Until the email service provider is configured,
              the signup form does not send your address anywhere. If you submit it, nothing
              happens.
            </td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-3">When live, until you unsubscribe</td>
            <td class="py-3">Consent</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h2>3. No cookies, no third-party trackers</h2>
    <p>
      This site sets no cookies on first visit. No Google Analytics. No Facebook pixel. No Twitter
      embeds. Web fonts are self-hosted — they are not loaded from Google or anywhere else. The only
      outbound calls are the two government / non-profit APIs listed above, and they only fire when
      you actively use the MP lookup.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      Under the UK GDPR you have rights of access, rectification, erasure, restriction, objection
      and portability. Because we hold almost no personal data, most of these are trivially
      satisfied — but if you have questions or a concern, email
      <a href={`mailto:${site.publisher.email}`}>{site.publisher.email}</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Right to complain</h2>
    <p>
      You have a right to complain to the UK Information Commissioner’s Office at any time —
      <a href="https://ico.org.uk/make-a-complaint/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"
        >ico.org.uk/make-a-complaint</a
      >.
    </p>

    <h2 id="accessibility">6. Accessibility statement</h2>
    <p>
      This site aims to meet WCAG 2.2 AA. If you encounter a barrier — a contrast issue, a missing
      label, anything that gets in your way — email <a href={`mailto:${site.publisher.email}`}
        >{site.publisher.email}</a
      >
      and we’ll fix it. Based on the AbilityNet model accessibility statement.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Updates to this notice</h2>
    <p>
      We will update this notice as the site changes. Material changes (such as adding the
      email-list provider) will be noted at the top of this page with a new “last updated” date.
    </p>
  </article>

  <section class="container-prose border-rule border-t py-10">
    <h2 class="font-display text-h2 text-ink font-semibold">Stay in the loop</h2>
    <p class="text-ink/85 mt-3">
      If you want occasional, low-volume updates on the Bill’s progress, you can sign up below. The
      form is GDPR-compliant: explicit consent, no pre-ticked boxes, no marketing list sharing.
      Submission is stubbed today — the email service provider is being chosen and the form will be
      wired once it’s in place.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-6">
      <EmailSignup client:visible />
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
